It&#8217;s understood a minibus taxi and an SUV crashed head on late on Saturday night, leaving all occupants in both vehicles dead. JOHANNESBURG - Thirteen people have been killed in a head-on collision on the R505 between Wolmaransstad and Ottosdal in the North West.It s understood a minibus taxi and an SUV crashed head on late on Saturday night, leaving all occupants in both vehicles dead.The Road Traffic Management Corporation (RTMC) says the exact cause of the crash is unknown at this stage.RTMC spokesperson Simon Zwane says, The RTMC is launching an investigation to try and understand what could have led to the accident. 